The paper discusses efficient string verification methods with low communication complexity, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography and information theory (cs.CR, cs.IT). The use of noise-based logic and mathematical analysis of error probability suggest a focus on logic and computation (cs.LO), while the mention of hash functions and string comparison suggest a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.DM).
